Date: 2001-06-22

Title: The boundary N=2 supersymmetric sine-Gordon model

Authors: Rafael I. Nepomechie

Comments: 10 pages, LaTeX; amssymb, no figures

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B516 (2001) 376-382

We construct an action for the N=2 supersymmetric sine-Gordon model on thehalf-line, which we argue is both supersymmetric and integrable. The boundaryinteraction depends on three continuous boundary parameters, as well as thebulk mass parameter.